
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-williams-websec-session-continue-prob-00.txt'>
    <title>"Hypertext Transport Protocol (HTTP) Session Continuation: Problem Statement", Nico Williams</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-williams-websec-session-continue-prob-00.txt</link>
    <description>One of the most often talked about problems in web security is "cookies".  Web cookies are a method of associating requests with "sessions" that may have been authenticated somehow.  Cookies are a form of bearer token that leave much to be desired.  This document describes the session "continuation" problem for the HyperText Transport Protocol (HTTP).</description>
    <dc:date>2012-12-31T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
